# My Frontend Helm Chart

This is a Helm chart for deploying a frontend application with a customizable title.

## Prerequisites

- Kubernetes 1.16+
- Helm 3+

## Installing the Chart

To install the chart, use the following command:

```bash
helm install my-frontend ./my-frontend
```

This will deploy the frontend application with the default settings.

To customize the deployment, you can use a values file. For example:

```bash
helm install my-frontend -f values.yaml ./my-frontend
```

## Configuration

The following table lists the configurable parameters of the My Frontend chart and their default values:
| Parameter | Description | Default |
| --------- | ----------- | ------- |
| replicaCount | Number of replicas | 1 |
| image.repository | Container image repository | "my-frontend" |
| image.tag | Container image tag | "latest" |
| image.pullPolicy | Container image pull policy | "IfNotPresent" |
| service.type | Kubernetes service type | ClusterIP |
| service.port | Kubernetes service port | 80 |
| frontend.titleConfigMapName | Name of ConfigMap containing the title | "my-frontend-title" |

Specify each parameter using the `--set key=value[,key=value]` argument to `helm install`, or use a values file with the `-f/--values` flag.

## Customizing the Title

To customize the title of the frontend application, create a ConfigMap with the desired title and specify the name of the ConfigMap in the `frontend.titleConfigMapName` parameter.

For example, to set the title to "My Custom Title", create a ConfigMap like this:

```yaml
apiVersion: v1
kind: ConfigMap
metadata:
  name: my-frontend-title
data:
  title: My Custom Title
```

And then install the chart like this:

```bash
helm install my-frontend --set frontend.titleConfigMapName=my-frontend-title ./my-frontend
```

## Uninstalling the Chart

To uninstall/delete the my-frontend deployment:

```bash
helm uninstall my-frontend
```

This will delete all resources associated with the chart.
